      "note": "Therein = in the curse. A curse is not a matter of words: it is a terrible spiritual state, opposite to the state of Grace. Can man curse? Not of course in the same sense in which we speak of the curse of Allah. A mere verbal curse is of no effect. Hence the English saying: \"A causeless curse will not come.\" But if men are oppressed or unjustly treated, their cries can ascend to Allah in prayer, and then it becomes Allah's \"wrath\" or curse, the deprivation of Allah's Grace as regards the wrongdoer."
